{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01K1ReP2bahfq6GqoGvtadSq","type":"tool_result","content":"   340→    const hasGarbledCamelCase = words.some(\n   341→      (w) =>\n   342→        w.length >= 3 &&\n   343→        w.length <= 7 &&\n   344→        /[a-z][A-Z]/.test(w) &&\n   345→        !/^(Mc|Mac)[A-Z]/.test(w)\n   346→    );\n   347→    if (hasGarbledCamelCase) {\n   348→      return true;\n   349→    }\n   350→  }\n   351→\n   352→  return false;\n   353→}\n   354→\n   355→const COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(beat|fold|stir|mix|add|pour|bake|cook|cool|remove|place|combine|whisk|knead|roll|spread|brush|slice|chop|dice|mince|drain|rinse|peel|grate|melt|simmer|boil|fry|sauté|saute|roast|grill|broil|steam|let|set|transfer|serve|garnish|arrange|sprinkle|season|preheat|cover|uncover|reduce|bring|toss|cut|trim|shape|form|scatter|score|pat|rub|skim|strain|heat|discard|rest|marinate|wrap|flip|turn|layer|stuff|drizzle|squeeze|zest|soak|thaw|freeze|chill|warm|toast|crush|pound|crack|break|separate|weigh|measure|sift|dust|coat|dip|dredge|baste|debone|butterfly|truss|shred|puree|blend|process|pulse|whip|cream|proof|rise|punch|divide|portion|assemble)\\b/i;\n   356→\n   357→// Polish imperative cooking verbs (with OCR-resilient forms — no diacritics required).\n   358→// These cover the most common recipe instruction starters. Includes common OCR-corrupted\n   359→// forms (e.g., \"Smaż\" → \"Smaz\", \"Dodaj\" → \"Dodaj\").\n   360→// Note: only verbs that NEVER start a recipe title. \"Piecz\" (bake) is excluded because\n   361→// \"Pieczeń\" (roast) and \"Pieczarki\" (mushrooms) share the prefix.\n   362→const POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS = /^(podawaj|dodaj|dodawaj|sma[zż]|gotuj|odced[zź]|wymieszaj|mieszaj|wlej|nalej|przygotuj|zagotuj|pokr[oó]j|obierz|wrzuc|wrzuć|usma[zż]|podsma[zż]|prze[lł][oó][zż]|zblenduj|ubij|roztrzepaj|rozprowad[zź]|wyrob|zamieszaj|posyp|polej|odstaw|na[lł][oó][zż]|przykryj|odkryj|wstaw|zdejmij|ods[aą]cz|rozgrzej|posiekaj|zetrzyj|wy[lł][oó][zż]|wyjmij|ukr[oó]j|przekr[oó]j|formuj|ugniataj|rozwałkuj|ugotuj|ugotowa[cć]|upiecz|podawa[cć]|zapiekaj|obtocz|obtoczy[cć]|podgrzej|podgrzewaj)\\b/i;\n   363→\n   364→function looksLikeCookingInstruction(text: string): boolean {\n   365→  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n   366→  if (words.length < 4) return false;  // Instructions are multi-word sentences\n   367→  if (COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS.test(text.trim())) return true;\n   368→  if (POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS.test(text.trim())) return true;\n   369→  return false;\n   370→}\n   371→\n   372→/**\n   373→ * A line starting with a lowercase letter and having 4+ words is prose continuation.\n   374→ * Recipe titles are capitalized (Title Case or ALL CAPS), so a lowercase-start line\n   375→ * is a strong signal for mid-recipe body text.\n   376→ */\n   377→function isBodyProse(line: string): boolean {\n   378→  return /^[a-ząćęłńóśźż]/.test(line) && wordCount(line) >= 4;\n   379→}\n   380→\n   381→/**\n   382→ * Detect pages where the OCR capture starts mid-recipe with no title present.\n   383→ * Returns true if the first 3 non-empty lines (after `startFrom`) are all ingredients,\n   384→ * cooking instructions, or body prose continuation text.\n   385→ */\n   386→function isTitleAbsentPage(lines: Array<string>, startFrom: number = 0): boolean {\n   387→  const relevantLines = startFrom > 0 ? lines.slice(startFrom) : lines;\n   388→  const nonEmptyLines = relevantLines.map(l => l.trim()).filter(l => l.length > 0);\n   389→\n   390→  if (nonEmptyLines.length < 3) return false;\n   391→\n   392→  const first3 = nonEmptyLines.slice(0, 3);\n   393→\n   394→  return first3.every(line =>\n   395→    looksLikeIngredient(line) ||\n   396→    looksLikeCookingInstruction(line) ||\n   397→    isBodyProse(line)\n   398→  );\n   399→}\n   400→\n   401→function passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n   402→  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n   403→  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n   404→  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n   405→  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n   406→  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n   407→  if (looksLikeCookingInstruction(text)) return false;\n   408→  // Pipe-separated lines are book category/chapter headers, not recipe titles\n   409→  if (text.includes(\" | \")) return false;\n   410→  // Trailing page number (e.g. \"VEGETABLE SIDES                         145\")\n   411→  if (/\\s{3,}\\d{1,4}\\s*$/.test(text)) return false;\n   412→  // Slash-separated breadcrumbs (e.g., \"/ Jesien / Zupy\") are navigation, not titles\n   413→  // Only filter when 2+ slashes are present — single-slash lines like\n   414→  // \"TITLE / SUBTITLE\" are legitimate continuation-merged titles\n   415→  if ((text.match(/\\//g) || []).length >= 2) return false;\n   416→  // Bullet-list items (ingredients or instruction steps) are never titles\n   417→  if (/^\\s*[-•*]\\s/.test(text)) return false;\n   418→  // \"For the sauce:\", \"For the filling:\" etc. are sub-section headers\n   419→  if (/^For the\\s+/i.test(text) && /:\\s*$/.test(text)) return false;\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HJ2D9yKwv8fHo4nTTyXQfw","session_id":"f8a76d47-7fe3-4af3-aeb1-bc54afe62ca5","uuid":"3406a823-efaa-4dc9-b2bf-fd2c70823da5"}
