{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HJ2D9yKwv8fHo4nTTyXQfw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have enough to provide a focused, thorough review. Here it is.\n\n---\n\n# Code Review: `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` expansion\n\n## Review Metrics\n- Files Reviewed: 1\n- Critical Issues: 0\n- High Priority: 1\n- Medium Priority: 2\n- Suggestions: 2\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nThe added verbs are linguistically correct and consistent with the existing pattern's style. One verb introduces a semantic overlap risk (`ugotowa[cć]` is an infinitive, not an imperative, which differs from the established convention). Two verbs have incomplete conjugation coverage compared to existing peers, which will cause missed matches.\n\n---\n\n## HIGH Priority\n\n### 1. `ugotowa[cć]` is an infinitive, breaking the imperative-only convention\n\n**File**: `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts:362`\n\nThe comment at line 358 explicitly states this regex covers \"Polish imperative cooking verbs.\" All 30+ existing entries are imperatives (`dodaj`, `wymieszaj`, `wlej`, `posyp`, etc.). `ugotowa[cć]` is the infinitive/perfective infinitive form (\"to cook\") and `podawa[cć]` is also an infinitive (\"to serve\").\n\nInfinitives do appear in recipe text, but they also appear in recipe _titles_ — e.g., \"Jak ugotować makaron\" (How to cook pasta) is a valid recipe title. Matching infinitives with this filter would incorrectly suppress such titles.\n\nThe imperative of `ugotować` is `ugotuj`, which is already included in this same commit. `ugotowa[cć]` is redundant at best and title-suppressing at worst. Similarly, `podawa[cć]` (infinitive) is added alongside `podawaj` (imperative present) — the imperative already covers the instruction-start case; the infinitive form is unnecessary and risky.\n\n**Recommendation**: Remove `ugotowa[cć]` and `podawa[cć]`. The imperatives `ugotuj` and `podawaj` already cover instruction starts correctly and `podawaj` was already in the original list.\n\n---\n\n## MEDIUM Priority\n\n### 2. `obtocz` / `obtoczy[cć]` — inconsistent completeness versus sibling verbs\n\n**File**: `title-extractor.ts:362`\n\nThe existing pattern handles OCR-corrupted forms and both perfective/imperfective verb pairs for many verbs. For example, `sma[zż]` covers both \"smaz\" and \"smaż\", and `usma[zż]` / `podsma[zż]` cover prefixed forms. The new entry `obtocz` covers only the perfective imperative (\"coat/dredge once\"). The imperfective counterpart `obtaczaj` (repeated/ongoing coating) is absent.\n\nWhether this matters depends on corpus frequency, but the omission is inconsistent with how sibling verbs like `gotuj` / `ugotuj` are both included for the same reason.\n\n### 3. `zapiekaj` has no perfective counterpart\n\n**File**: `title-extractor.ts:362`\n\n`zapiekaj` is the imperfective imperative (\"keep baking/bake repeatedly\"). The perfective imperative `zapiecz` (\"bake it [once]\") is absent. By contrast, `upiecz` (perfective of `piec`) _is_ included. A recipe step like \"Zapiecz w piekarniku przez 20 minut\" would be missed. This is the same incompleteness pattern as point 2.\n\n---\n\n## LOW Priority (Suggestions)\n\n### 4. `podawaj` was already present before this commit\n\nThe original regex already contained `podawaj` as the first alternative. Adding `podawa[cć]` (see HIGH priority note above) makes the existing `podawaj` entry visually overshadowed. If the infinitive forms are removed, no change is needed here — but it is worth noting that `podawaj` has been in the list since before this change and is not a new addition.\n\n### 5. Consider a sorted/grouped structure for long-term maintainability\n\nThe regex is now 33 alternatives on a single line exceeding 400 characters. The comment at line 357–361 is good, but the regex itself has no grouping by category (prep verbs, heat verbs, finishing verbs, etc.). This is not urgent — the `COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` English equivalent follows the same style — but as this list grows toward 50+ entries, a builder pattern with comments would make auditing verb coverage far easier.\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- The diacritic-optional pattern (`sma[zż]`, `[cć]`, `[oó]`) is applied consistently to the new verbs that need it (`obtoczy[cć]`, `podawa[cć]`).\n- The `\\b` word boundary at the end is preserved, which correctly prevents prefix matches on nouns sharing a stem.\n- `upiecz` is a well-chosen addition — it is prefixed enough to avoid the `Pieczeń`/`Pieczarki` collision problem called out in the comment for `Piecz`.\n- `podgrzej` / `podgrzewaj` are a correct imperfective/perfective pair, properly paired unlike some other new entries."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aef83498b29e75f26 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 14419\ntool_uses: 2\nduration_ms: 38553</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f8a76d47-7fe3-4af3-aeb1-bc54afe62ca5","uuid":"ea1fe9d5-f02d-42c5-a8e8-f01feff2a9a1","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Review this change to `/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts`.\n\nThe only change made was expanding the `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` regex constant (around line 362) by adding these verb alternations to the end:\n`ugotuj|ugotowa[cć]|upiecz|podawa[cć]|zapiekaj|obtocz|obtoczy[cć]|podgrzej|podgrzewaj`\n\nPlease review:\n1. Implementation completeness - does it do what it claims?\n2. Code quality - is it consistent with existing patterns?\n3. Integration - should it be refactored into abstractions?\n4. Codebase consistency - any issues?\n\nRead the relevant section of the file and provide a focused review.","agentId":"aef83498b29e75f26","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have enough to provide a focused, thorough review. Here it is.\n\n---\n\n# Code Review: `POLISH_COOKING_INSTRUCTION_STARTS` expansion\n\n## Review Metrics\n- Files Rev