{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013nFXwPb2QNaug26aPmQX9m","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The review raised a valid concern about `ugotowa[cć]` and `podawa[cć]` being infinitives rather than imperatives, which could theoretically suppress title candidates like \"Jak ugotować makaron\". However:\n\n- `Jak ugotować...` starts with `Jak`, not `ugotować` — the regex anchors at `^`, so this is safe\n- A bare `Ugotować ziemniaki` or `Podawać letni...` as a recipe title is highly unusual in practice\n- The task spec explicitly requested these forms, and both match real instruction patterns in recipe body text\n\nThe other findings (missing `obtaczaj`, missing `zapiecz`) are legitimate gaps but were not part of the task scope — adding them would go beyond what was requested.\n\nThe change is correct as implemented. All 37 tests pass and the new verbs follow the existing diacritic-optional pattern style consistently."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1902,"cache_read_input_tokens":24880,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1902},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f8a76d47-7fe3-4af3-aeb1-bc54afe62ca5","uuid":"d40f21e5-94ed-408e-bd8a-ba102d9219b9"}
